{"body":"## Summary\n\nReplace issue #712's phrase-gated tool routing with seed-backed semantic frames and typed argument evidence across fetch, search, edit, and write capabilities.\n\nFixes #712.\n\n## Root cause\n\nThe planner had overlapping sources of truth: narrow natural-language probes could recognize a few surface forms, while separate hardcoded gates decided whether executable arguments were valid. Small paraphrases therefore bypassed the advertised tool, and declarative file creation could be stolen by the read router.\n\nThe initial PR draft added more reported templates. Maintainer feedback correctly identified that as another instance of the same failure class, so this revision removes those templates and generalizes the routing model.\n\n## Implementation\n\n- Compose seed-defined action, source, topic, target, and content roles with typed argument shapes: normalized URL, non-empty search topic, safe path plus old/new spans, or safe path plus literal payload.\n- Use the executable write parser as the single write-classification gate; remove the duplicate hardcoded `WRITE_VERBS` authority.\n- Recognize typed search leads only at the prompt boundary, after a seeded question opener, or after a complete seeded source phrase. This preserves valid question/source searches without stealing unrelated mid-sentence words.\n- Keep native Rust and browser-worker routing structurally aligned across Chat Completions, Responses, and Gemini.\n- Persist routing observations and semantic amendments in an associative links network. Formal AI ranks them through `AssociativeMemory` and writes a derived learning report whose promotion remains explicitly human-review gated.\n- Preserve the red/green investigation, self-coding patches, case study, and a fresh external Agent CLI event stream/report under `docs/case-studies/issue-712/`.\n- Add a real Agent CLI release E2E for declarative file creation.\n\nNo reported issue sentence is stored as a runtime template, and no new dependency is introduced.\n\n## Reproduction and verification\n\n- `tests/issue_712.rs` reproduces the reported matrix and adds unseen paraphrases plus negative boundaries to prevent memorization.\n- `tests/integration/issue_712_intent_routing.rs` verifies the production server through Chat Completions, Responses, and Gemini, including multilingual edit routing.\n- `tests/unit/issue_712_routing_learning.rs` verifies derived associative ranking, the review gate, and in-repo Agent CLI execution.\n- `tests/unit/docs_requirements_issue_712.rs` guards the semantic-routing contract and rejects issue-sentence templates in the seed.\n- The external Agent CLI independently ingested six linked observations/amendments, wrote the learning artifact, verified it, and left promotion awaiting review.\n\nLocal checks on the final commit after merging `main` v0.295.0:\n\n```text\ncargo test --all-features -- --test-threads=2\n  integration:   100 passed\n  issue #712:      7 passed\n  specification: 475 passed\n  unit:          1635 passed, 2 ignored\n\ncargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings\ncargo fmt --all -- --check\nnode --check src/web/worker/formal_ai_worker_16.js\nnode --check src/web/worker/formal_ai_worker_17.js\nnode experiments/issue_711_rebuild_changelog.mjs --check\n```\n\nThe v0.295.0 merge exposed a release-checker regression: release commits now consume fragments, while reconstruction inspected only their post-consumption tree. The checker now reads both sides of a release commit, the 397-fragment release map is canonical again, and duplicated v0.295.0 notes were removed without dropping their original release sections.\n","commits":[{"authoredDate":"2026-07-14T21:39:49Z","authors":[{"email":"drakonard@gmail.com","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","login":"konard","name":"konard"}],"committedDate":"2026-07-14T21:39:49Z","messageBody":"Adding .gitkeep for PR creation (default mode).\nThis file will be removed when the task is complete.\n\nIssue: https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/712","messageHeadline":"Initial commit with task details","oid":"aabd9c591ce0b6bdb15915edb1b784631b854881"},{"authoredDate":"2026-07-14T22:03:14Z","authors":[{"email":"drakonard@gmail.com","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","login":"konard","name":"konard"}],"committedDate":"2026-07-14T22:03:14Z","messageBody":"","messageHeadline":"test(agentic): reproduce issue 712 phrasing regressions","oid":"eda00462a1fcab94a98a083d993fbc526eda4563"},{"authoredDate":"2026-07-14T22:14:27Z","authors":[{"email":"drakonard@gmail.com","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","login":"konard","name":"konard"}],"committedDate":"2026-07-14T22:14:27Z","messageBody":"","messageHeadline":"fix(agentic): generalize tool intent routing","oid":"10c942c69cf2de83205f0390667a8dd9cb4ff991"},{"authoredDate":"2026-07-14T22:18:22Z","authors":[{"email":"drakonard@gmail.com","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","login":"konard","name":"konard"}],"committedDate":"2026-07-14T22:18:22Z","messageBody":"","messageHeadline":"test(api): cover issue 712 across tool surfaces","oid":"e928ef53e99e5d0c1505a72454661069be9c3ea4"},{"authoredDate":"2026-07-14T22:22:48Z","authors":[{"email":"drakonard@gmail.com","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","login":"konard","name":"konard"}],"committedDate":"2026-07-14T22:22:48Z","messageBody":"","messageHeadline":"ci(agent): exercise issue 712 new-file phrasing","oid":"624b92444d9da61e2b3ace0d7866a66b42cdb2ff"},{"authoredDate":"2026-07-14T22:22:48Z","authors":[{"email":"drakonard@gmail.com","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","login":"konard","name":"konard"}],"committedDate":"2026-07-14T22:22:48Z","messageBody":"","messageHeadline":"docs: preserve issue 712 self-coding evidence","oid":"81c90e9989795aa0453f0268b8f424d7ff462b68"},{"authoredDate":"2026-07-14T22:23:39Z","authors":[{"email":"drakonard@gmail.com","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","login":"konard","name":"konard"}],"committedDate":"2026-07-14T22:23:39Z","messageBody":"","messageHeadline":"chore: remove branch bootstrap placeholder